The Westman Super League of Curling standings got a lot tighter on Wednesday night. 
Terry McNamee and Cale Dunbar both fell in their games, creating a seven-way tie for first at 2-1 with Kelly McMechan, Steve Irwin, Duane Lang, Kelly Marnoch and Jerry Chudley. McNamee fell 7-6 to Marnoch while Dunbar dropped a 5-2 decision to Irwin. Please subscribe to view full article.
